    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-29T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-29T10:00:00-05:00" n="407"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">784A.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/2–2952:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 407<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d407fn1">Repeated to Paris, London, Ankara, Beirut,
                        Damascus, Amman, Cairo, Baghdad, and Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-02-29T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 29, 1952—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>894. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 881<note n="2" xml:id="d407fn2">
                        <ref target="#d405">Document 405</ref>.</note> and <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 623 Feb 28<note n="3" xml:id="d407fn3"
                        >Telegram 623 to Tel Aviv, Feb. 28, stated that the Israeli Embassy in
                        Washington had informed the Department that General <persName
                            corresp="#p_YMG1">Yadin</persName>, the Israeli Chief of Staff, was
                        meeting Colonel Salim, the Lebanese Chief of Staff, on Feb. 28 at the
                        latter’s request, with General <persName corresp="#p_RLG1">Riley</persName>
                        present. The Department requested the comment of the Embassy in Israel.
                        (683A.84A/2–2852)</note> re mtg Chief of Staff Gen <persName
                        corresp="#p_YMG1">Yadin</persName> with <gloss target="#t_Leb1">Leb</gloss>
                    Rep yesterday at Ras En Nakoura.</p>
                <p>Acting Dir Gen Fon Off <persName corresp="#p_CM1">Comay</persName> states mtg at
                    which Gen <persName corresp="#p_RLG1">Riley</persName> present was “very
                    satisfactory” both as to atmosphere and substantial results. Parties agreed sign
                    mutual undertaking re ships in distress similar to agreement concluded with
                    Syria. Matter will be cleared with next mtg of <gloss target="#t_MAC1"
                        >MAC</gloss> expected take place near future, perhaps next week. Agreement
                    wld be extended to ships belonging to third countries other than Egypt, Jordan
                    or Syria, latter’s point not to be included in formal agreement but made of
                    record by communications from Gen. <persName corresp="#p_RLG1"
                    >Riley</persName>.</p>
                <p>It was agreed further to settle claims arising from sale in <gloss
                        target="#t_Leb1">Leb</gloss> of cargo destined for Israel on one hand, and
                    seizure of several flocks of sheep by Israel. First flock seized is to be
                    retained in compensation <pb facs="0941" n="901" xml:id="pg_901"/> for cargo
                    while others are to be returned or corresponding compensation made.</p>
                <p>Source added that progress had been made in arranging to permit certain persons
                    of Jewish faith to emigrate from <gloss target="#t_Leb1">Leb</gloss> but
                    detailed report on this subj not yet recd by Fon Off.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
